From: Luis Henriques <lhenriques@suse.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jul 2019 15:32:21 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ceph: fix buffer free while holding i_ceph_lock in
 __ceph_build_xattrs_blob()
References: bnc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.2.14
Git-commit: 12fe3dda7ed89c95cc0ef7abc001ad1ad3e092f8

[ Upstream commit 12fe3dda7ed89c95cc0ef7abc001ad1ad3e092f8 ]

Calling ceph_buffer_put() in __ceph_build_xattrs_blob() may result in
freeing the i_xattrs.blob buffer while holding the i_ceph_lock.  This can
be fixed by having this function returning the old blob buffer and have
the callers of this function freeing it when the lock is released.

